hadiths[22]{hadithnumber,text,reference_book,reference_hadith,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro,urdu,chapter_title_arabic}:
3904,"Narrated AbuHurayrah: The Prophet (ﷺ) said: If anyone resorts to a diviner and believes in what he says (according) to the version of Musa), or has intercourse with his wife (according to the agreed version) when she is menstruating, or has intercourse with his wife through her anus, he has nothing to do with what has been sent down to Muhammad (ﷺ) - according to the version of Musaddad",30,1,,,,,,"ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جو کسی کاہن کے پاس آئے پ",3904,
3905,"Narrated Abdullah ibn Abbas: The Prophet (ﷺ) said: If anyone acquires any knowledge of astrology, he acquires a branch of magic of which he gets more as long as he continues to do so",30,2,,,,,,"عبداللہ بن عباس رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جس نے علم نجوم کا ",3905,
3906,"Narrated Zaid bin Khalid Al-Juhani:The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) led us in the morning prayer at al-Hudaibiyyah after rain which has fallen during the night, and when he finished, he turned to the people and said: Do you know what your Lord has said ? They said: Allah and His Apostle know best. He said: This morning there were among mt servants one who believes in me and one who disbelieves. The one who said: ""We have been given rain by Allah's grace and mercy"" is the one who believes in me and disbelieves in the star ; but the one who said: ""We have been given rain by such and such a rain star,"" is the one who disbelieves in me and believes in the star",30,3,,,,,,زید بن خالد جہنی رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے حدیبیہ میں ہمیں نماز فجر بار,3906,
3907,"Narrated Qabisah: I heard the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) say: Augury from the flight of birds, taking evil omens and the practice of pressomancy pertain to divination. Tarq: It is used in the sense of divination in which women threw stones. 'Iyafah: It means geomancy by drawing lines",30,4,,,,,,"قبیصہ بن وقاص رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں  میں نے رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کو فرماتے ہوئے سنا:  رمل، ب",3907,
3908,"Narrated Muhammed b. Ja'far:On the authority of 'Awf: 'Iyafah means to makes the birds fly by threatening them. Tarq means lines drawn on the earth",30,5,,,,,,عوف کہتے ہیں  «عيافة» سے مراد پرندہ اڑانا ہے اور «طرق» سے مراد وہ لکیریں ہیں جو زمین پر کھینچی جاتی ,3908,
3909,"Narrated Mu'awiyah b. al-Hakam al-Sulami:I said: Messenger of Allah! among us there are men who practice divination by drawing lines. He said: There was a Prophet who drew lines, so if anyone does it as he drew lines, that is right",30,6,,,,,,"معاویہ بن حکم سلمی رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں  میں نے عرض کیا: اللہ کے رسول! ہم میں کچھ لوگ ایسے ہیں جو خ",3909,
3910,"Narrated Abdullah ibn Mas'ud: The Prophet (ﷺ) said: Taking omens is polytheism; taking omens is polytheism. He said it three times. Every one of us has some, but Allah removes it by trust (in Him)",30,7,,,,,,"عبداللہ بن مسعود رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے تین بار فرمایا:  بدشگو",3910,
3911,"Narrated Abu Hurairah: The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) as saying : There is no infection, no evil, omen or serpent, in a hungry belly and no hamah. A nomadic Arab asked: How is it that when camels are in the sand as if they were gazelles and a mangy camel comes among them and it gives them mange ? He replied: Who infected the first one ? Ma'mar, quoting al-Zuhri said: A man told me that Abu Hurairah narrated to him saying that he heard the Prophet (ﷺ) say: A diseased camel should not be brought with a healthy camel to drink water. He said: The man then consulted him and said: Did you not tell us that Prophet (ﷺ) had said: There is no infection, no serpent in a hungry belly and no hamah? He replied: I did not transmit it to you. Al-Zuhri said: Abu Salamah said: He had narrated it and I did not hear that Abu Hurairah had ever forgotten any tradition except this one. Note: The majority of scholars interpret this to mean that these things in and of themselves do not transmit or cause harm through supernatural or hidden means but that Allah is ultimately in control and any fearful superstition around these is false",30,8,,,,,,"ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  نہ کسی کو کسی کی بیماری ",3911,
3912,"Narrated Abu Hurairah:The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) as saying: There is no infection, no hamah, no other promising rain, and no serpent in a hungry belly",30,9,,,,,,"ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  نہ کسی کو کسی کی بیماری ",3912,
3913,"Narrated AbuHurayrah: The Prophet (ﷺ) said: There is no ghoul",30,10,,,,,,"ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  بھوت پریت کو کسی کو نقصا",3913,
3914,"Abu Dawud said:Malik was asked about the meaning of his saying: There is no safar. He replied: The people of pre-Islamic Arabia used to make the month of safar lawful (for war). They made it lawful in one year and unlawful in another year. The Prophet (ﷺ) said: There is no safar",30,11,,,,,,ابوداؤد کہتے ہیں  حارث بن مسکین پر پڑھا گیا، اور میں موجود تھا کہ اشہب نے آپ کو خبر دی ہے کہ امام ما,3914,
3915,"Muhammad b. al-Musaffa said to us on the authority of Baqiyyah. He said:I asked Muhammad b. Rashid about the meaning of the word hamah. He replied: The pre-Islamic Arabs used to say: When anyone dies and is buried, a bird comes forth from his grave. I asked: What did he mean by safar ? He said: I heard that the pre-Islamic Arabs used to take evil omen from safar. So the Prophet (ﷺ) said: There is no safar. Muhammad (b. Rashid) said: We heard someone say: It is a pain in the stomach. They said that it was infection. Hence he said: There is no safar",30,12,,,,,,"انس رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  نہ کسی کو کسی کی بیماری لگتی ہ",3915,
3916,"Narrated Anas:The Prophet (ﷺ) as saying: There is no infection* and no evil omen, and I like a good omen. Good omen means a good word. * The majority of scholars interpret this to mean that these things in and of themselves do not transmit or cause harm through supernatural or hidden means but that Allah is ultimately in control and any fearful superstition around these is false",30,13,,,,,,بقیہ کہتے ہیں کہ  میں نے محمد بن راشد سے پوچھا کہ نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے قول «هام» کے کیا مع,3916,
3917,"Narrated AbuHurayrah: When the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) heard a word, and he liked it, he said: We took your omen from your mouth",30,14,,,,,,ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے ایک بات سنی جو آپ کو بھلی لگی تو ,3917,
3918,"Narrated 'Ata:People said: safar is a pain within the belly. I asked: What is hamah ? He said: People said (believed) that hamah which is an owl or a nightbird and which shrieks is the spirit of men. It is not the spirit of men. It is an animal",30,15,,,,,,"عطاء سے روایت ہے کہ لوگ کہتے تھے کہ  صفر ایک قسم کا درد ہے جو پیٹ میں ہوتا ہے تو میں نے پوچھا: ہامہ ",3918,
3919,"Narrated Urwah ibn Amir al-Qurashi: When taking omens was mentioned in the presence of the Prophet (ﷺ), he said: The best type is the good omen, and it does not turn back a Muslim. If one of you sees anything he dislikes, he should say: O Allah, no one brings good things except Thee, and no one averts evil things except Thee and there is no might and power but in Allah",30,16,,,,,,عروہ بن عامر قرشی کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے پاس طیرہ  ( بدشگونی )  کا ذکر کیا گیا,3919,
3920,"Narrated Buraydah ibn al-Hasib: The Prophet (ﷺ) did not take omens from anything, but when he sent out an agent he asked about his name. If it pleased him, he was glad about it, and his cheerfulness on that account was visible in his face. If he disliked his name, his displeasure on that account was visible in his face. When he entered a village, he asked about its name, and if it pleased him, he was glad about it, and his cheerfulness on that account was visible in his face. But if he disliked its name, his displeasure on that account was visible in his face",30,17,,,,,,بریدہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کسی چیز سے فال بد  ( بدشگونی )  نہیں لیت,3920,
3921,"Narrated Sa'd ibn Malik: The Prophet (ﷺ) said: There is no hamah, no infection and no evil omen; if there is in anything an evil omen, it is a house, a horse, and a woman",30,18,,,,,,"سعد بن مالک رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم فرماتے تھے:  مردے کی روح جانور کی",3921,
3922,"It was narrated from 'Abdullah bin 'Umar that the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said:""An omen is in a dwelling, a woman or a horse."" Abu Dawud said: This tradition was read out to al-Harith b. Miskin and I was witness. It was said to him that Ibn Qasim told him that Malik was asked about evil omen in a horse and in a house. He replied: There are many houses in which people lived and perished and again others lived therein and they also perished. This is its explanation so far as we know. Allah knows best. Abu Dawud said: 'Umar (ra) said: A mat in a house better than a woman who does not give birth to a child",30,19,,,,,,"عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  نحوست گھر، عورت ",3922,
3923,"Yahya ibn Abdullah ibn Buhayr said that he was informed by one who had heard Farwah ibn Musayk tell that he said:Messenger of Allah! we have land called Abyan, which is the land where we have our fields and grow our crops, but it is very unhealthy. The Prophet (ﷺ) said: Leave it, for destruction comes from being near disease",30,20,,,,,,"فروہ بن مسیک رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  میں نے عرض کیا: اللہ کے رسول! ہمارے پاس ایک زمین ہے جسے ابین ",3923,
3924,"Narrated Anas ibn Malik: A man said: Messenger of Allah! we were in an abode in which our numbers and our goods were many and changed to an abode in which our numbers and our goods became few. The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said: Leave it, for it is reprehensible",30,21,,,,,,"انس بن مالک رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  ایک شخص نے عرض کیا: اللہ کے رسول! ہم ایک گھر میں تھے تو اس میں",3924,
3925,"Narrated Jabir ibn Abdullah: The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) took a man who was suffering from tubercular leprosy by the hand; he then put it along with his own hand in the dish and said: Eat with confidence in Allah and trust in Him",30,22,,,,,,جابر رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے ایک کوڑھی کا ہاتھ پکڑ کر اپنے ساتھ پی,3925,
